    "text": "Maize-peanut intercropping enhanced carbon fixation and carboxylation in maize leaves compared to maize monocropping. In intercropping, apparent quantum yield (AQY), light-saturated net photosynthetic rate (LSPn), light saturation point (LSP), and light compensation point (LCP) increased by 11.6%, 9.4%, 8.9%, and 32.1%, respectively. Carboxylation efficiency (CE), CO2 saturation point (Cisat), Rubisco maximum carboxylation rate (Vcmax), maximum electron transfer rate (Jmax), and triose phosphate utilization rate (TPU) increased by 28.5%, 7.3%, 18.7%, 29.2%, and 17.0%, respectively. The CO2 compensation point (Γ) decreased by 22.6%.",
